Broadway, west side, north from West 53rd Street, showing prominently two 12-story structures, 828-830 and 832-838. The first of these, houses the Manhattan Music Hall and the latter the Hotel Cumberland (formerly the Adlon). The hotel is directly at the S.W. corner of West 54th Street. This set consists of a negative and a positive view.

September 1935.

W.P.A. Photo.
